Figure 7c shows the charge-discharge curves of the NiCo2S4 electrode at 1–5 mAcm−1 current densities. Based on the charge-discharge curves of the NiCo2S4 electrode, we found that the mirror image of the sample corresponded to the redox reactions during the electrochemical process. In addition, we observed that as the current density increased, the discharge time decreased. The specific capacitances were calculated based on these charge-discharge curves using the following equation:1C=I×Δtm×ΔV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
